{{Han etym}}

In the oracle bone script, it is a {{Han compound|八|口|人|ls=ic|t1=speech; breath|t2=mouth|t3=person|nocap=1}} – speech; original character of {{och-l|說|id=2|to speak}}. It is also a {{Han compound|㕣|人|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=person|nocap=1}}.

Alternatively, {{zh-l|*八}} may be interpreted as smile lines above the mouth (Gao Hongjin) or as meaning “to divide” (Lin Yiguang, i.e. the mouth is divided when smiling); in either case, the character would be the original character of {{och-l|悅|pleased|id=1}}.

